(firstQuint)Trial of Weaning of Nasal Continuous Positive Airway Pressure (CPAP).

 Objective: To study the weight and the post menstrual age (PMA) at the time of nasal CPAP (NCPAP) wean utilizing the method of sudden wean as compared to gradual wean.

 .

 Methods: A prospective randomized trial was conducted comparing sudden weaning with gradual weaning from NCPAP in neonates with gestational age (GA) <32 weeks.

 The patients were randomized to one of the two methods of weaning from NCPAP and their success was compared.

